1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:03,680
Hello everyone and welcome to EnglishPod.
大家好，欢迎收听EnglishPod。

2
00:00:03,680 --> 00:00:04,760
My name is Marco.
我是Marco。

3
00:00:04,760 --> 00:00:09,220
My name is Catherine and today we have a lesson that comes actually from a user request.
我是Catherine，今天我们这节课其实是来自一位用户的请求。

4
00:00:09,220 --> 00:00:10,220
That's right.
没错。

5
00:00:10,220 --> 00:00:15,800
We had a user request who asked us if we can do something about a purchasing manager, maybe
有位用户问我们能不能做一期关于采购经理的内容，也许

6
00:00:15,800 --> 00:00:20,360
what his job does or what it is to be a purchasing manager.
讲讲他的工作内容或者采购经理是做什么的。

7
00:00:20,360 --> 00:00:22,940
So you'll find out all about that today in this lesson.
所以今天这节课你会了解到所有相关内容。

8
00:00:22,940 --> 00:00:26,960
It's an upper intermediate about being a purchasing manager and about vendors.
这是一节中高级课程，关于采购经理和供应商。

9
00:00:26,960 --> 00:00:31,160
So let's check out today's dialogue.
那我们来看看今天的对话吧。

10
00:00:31,160 --> 00:00:37,520
Good morning, Angela.
早上好，Angela。

11
00:00:37,520 --> 00:00:39,320
How have you been lately?
你最近怎么样？

12
00:00:39,320 --> 00:00:40,320
Morning Michael.
早上好，Michael。

13
00:00:40,320 --> 00:00:42,340
I've been very busy lately.
我最近一直很忙。

14
00:00:42,340 --> 00:00:47,360
One of our other vendors is going out of business and I've been searching for a suitable replacement.
我们其中一个供应商要倒闭了，我一直在找合适的替代者。

15
00:00:47,360 --> 00:00:50,820
Well rest assured that you can count on us to be here for the long run.
放心吧，你可以信赖我们，我们会长期合作。

16
00:00:50,820 --> 00:00:51,820
Please sit down.
请坐。

17
00:00:51,820 --> 00:00:52,820
Coffee?
喝咖啡吗？

18
00:00:52,820 --> 00:00:53,820
No thanks.
不了，谢谢。

19
00:00:53,820 --> 00:00:56,360
I've been trying to cut down on the caffeine.
我一直在试着减少咖啡因摄入。

20
00:00:56,360 --> 00:00:58,080
I could never do that.
我可做不到。

21
00:00:58,080 --> 00:01:01,220
I'd be a zombie if I didn't have my morning coffee fix.
如果早上不喝杯咖啡提神，我就像个僵尸。

22
00:01:01,220 --> 00:01:02,940
Let's get down to business then.
那我们谈正事吧。

23
00:01:02,940 --> 00:01:03,940
Yes.
好的。

24
00:01:03,940 --> 00:01:09,240
I've come to talk with you about ordering the 8 megapixel cameras for our new MiPhone.
我来是想跟你谈谈为我们新款MiPhone订购800万像素摄像头的事。

25
00:01:09,240 --> 00:01:14,260
The demand for phone cameras is growing and Pear has been falling behind in the market.
手机摄像头的需求在增长，而Pear在市场上已经落后了。

26
00:01:14,260 --> 00:01:15,260
That's great.
太好了。

27
00:01:15,260 --> 00:01:18,320
I'm glad to hear that Pear has finally jumped on the bandwagon.
我很高兴听到Pear终于跟上了潮流。

28
00:01:18,320 --> 00:01:21,400
Right now our contract is for the 5 megapixel cameras.
目前我们的合同是500万像素摄像头。

29
00:01:21,400 --> 00:01:23,600
Is Pear still interested in having those?
Pear还有兴趣要那些吗？

30
00:01:23,600 --> 00:01:24,600
No.
不。

31
00:01:24,600 --> 00:01:27,760
We're changing all the cameras to 8 megapixels.
我们要把所有摄像头换成800万像素。

32
00:01:27,760 --> 00:01:32,960
We were hoping that by making your company our sole supplier for cameras, we could negotiate
我们希望让贵公司成为我们摄像头的独家供应商，这样我们可以协商

33
00:01:32,960 --> 00:01:34,120
a better deal.
一个更好的价格。

34
00:01:34,120 --> 00:01:35,120
Surely.
当然。

35
00:01:35,120 --> 00:01:42,040
Let's get started by drafting a new contract.
我们开始起草一份新合同吧。

36
00:01:42,040 --> 00:01:43,040
Alright we're back.
好了，我们回来了。

37
00:01:43,040 --> 00:01:45,640
So a very interesting job to be a purchasing manager.
采购经理这个工作真有意思。

38
00:01:45,640 --> 00:01:48,240
A lot of responsibility on top of him.
他肩上责任很大。

39
00:01:48,240 --> 00:01:53,240
And we actually saw some really interesting phrases and words that are related to business,
我们确实看到了一些非常有趣的短语和词汇，跟商务、

40
00:01:53,240 --> 00:01:55,920
to negotiating, contracts, etc.
谈判、合同等有关。

41
00:01:55,920 --> 00:02:03,680
So let's take a look at some of those now on Language Takeaway.
那我们现在来看看语言要点中的一些内容。

42
00:02:03,680 --> 00:02:05,680
The first word we have is vendor.
第一个词是vendor。

43
00:02:05,680 --> 00:02:06,680
This is a noun.
这是一个名词。

44
00:02:06,680 --> 00:02:08,480
It means it's a job.
它指的是一种职业。

45
00:02:08,480 --> 00:02:10,200
It's the name of a person's job.
是某个人的职业名称。

46
00:02:10,200 --> 00:02:12,040
So he is a vendor.
所以他是个vendor。

47
00:02:12,040 --> 00:02:13,960
And a vendor, what does a vendor do?
那vendor是做什么的？

48
00:02:13,960 --> 00:02:16,720
Well, a vendor sells things.
嗯，vendor是卖东西的人。

49
00:02:16,720 --> 00:02:21,720
So the verb here is to vend, like a vending machine is that machine that you can buy sodas
所以这里的动词是to vend，就像自动售货机（vending machine）是那种你可以买汽水的机器。

50
00:02:21,720 --> 00:02:22,720
from.


51
00:02:22,720 --> 00:02:25,280
So a vendor is someone who sells things to someone else.
所以vendor是把东西卖给其他人的人。

52
00:02:25,280 --> 00:02:29,760
Okay so I can say he is a door vendor.
好的，那我可以说他是个卖门的vendor。

53
00:02:29,760 --> 00:02:30,760
He sells doors?
他卖门？

54
00:02:30,760 --> 00:02:31,760
Yeah, that's right.
是的，没错。

55
00:02:31,760 --> 00:02:36,240
Or let me contact my vendor about the price list for these TVs.
或者让我联系我的vendor，问问这些电视的价格表。

56
00:02:36,240 --> 00:02:37,400
Okay, very good.
好的，非常好。

57
00:02:37,400 --> 00:02:40,840
So we're talking about a vendor who is going out of business.
所以我们说的是一个要倒闭的vendor。

58
00:02:40,840 --> 00:02:45,880
And because he's going out of business, this manager is actually looking for a suitable
因为他要倒闭了，这位经理正在找一个合适的

59
00:02:45,880 --> 00:02:47,120
replacement.
替代者。

60
00:02:47,120 --> 00:02:50,860
So this is an interesting phrase because these two words normally go together.
这是一个有趣的短语，因为这两个词通常一起出现。

61
00:02:50,860 --> 00:02:56,160
We say let's find a replacement, okay that's good, but really we want a suitable replacement.
我们说找个替代者，这没问题，但我们真正想要的是合适的替代者。

62
00:02:56,160 --> 00:02:59,280
And so first of all, the word suitable means like appropriate or good.
首先，suitable这个词意思是合适的或好的。

63
00:02:59,280 --> 00:03:00,280
But what about replacement?
那replacement呢？

64
00:03:00,280 --> 00:03:01,280
What does this mean?
这是什么意思？

65
00:03:01,280 --> 00:03:03,920
A replacement is something that takes the place of.
Replacement是替代某物的东西。

66
00:03:03,920 --> 00:03:05,800
It replaces something else.
它替换别的东西。

67
00:03:05,800 --> 00:03:09,100
So for example, we have our vendor who went out of business.
比如，我们的vendor倒闭了。

68
00:03:09,100 --> 00:03:14,360
So what we are looking now for is another vendor, but not just any vendor, a suitable
所以我们现在找的是另一个vendor，但不是随便一个，而是合适的

69
00:03:14,360 --> 00:03:19,000
vendor, one that has the things that we need or the prices that we need.
vendor，一个拥有我们需要的东西或价格的。

70
00:03:19,000 --> 00:03:21,400
And in order to replace the one that went out of business.
为了替换那个倒闭的。

71
00:03:21,400 --> 00:03:24,680
Right, so we can say this about other things, not just people.
对，所以我们可以用这个来说其他东西，不只是人。

72
00:03:24,680 --> 00:03:31,080
For example, if I break my iPhone, my cell phone, very expensive phone, I'm upset about
比如，如果我摔坏我的iPhone，我的手机，很贵的手机，我会很郁闷。

73
00:03:31,080 --> 00:03:32,080
it.


74
00:03:32,080 --> 00:03:33,680
But when I buy a new one, I don't want a cheap one.
但当我买新的时，我不想要便宜的。

75
00:03:33,680 --> 00:03:37,640
I want a suitable replacement, one that's about the same as the old one.
我想要一个合适的替代品，跟旧的差不多。

76
00:03:37,640 --> 00:03:38,640
That's right.
没错。

77
00:03:38,640 --> 00:03:42,600
So maybe you don't get the exact same one, but you get one that's very similar.
所以可能不是完全一样的，但非常相似。

78
00:03:42,600 --> 00:03:43,600
Exactly.
正是。

79
00:03:43,600 --> 00:03:44,600
Okay, very good.
好的，非常好。

80
00:03:44,600 --> 00:03:48,600
So now they're going to talk a little bit about the contract, but they kind of do a
现在他们要谈一点合同的事，但他们有点

81
00:03:48,600 --> 00:03:52,800
little bit of small talk and they're talking about coffee and he says, well, you know,
他们聊了点闲话，谈到咖啡，他说，嗯，你知道，

82
00:03:52,800 --> 00:03:56,400
I'd be a zombie if I didn't have my morning coffee fix.
如果早上不喝杯咖啡提神，我就像个僵尸一样。

83
00:03:56,400 --> 00:03:57,680
I know how that feels.
我懂那种感觉。

84
00:03:57,680 --> 00:04:01,280
This is a person who loves to drink caffeine to wake up.
这是一个喜欢喝咖啡因来提神的人。

85
00:04:01,280 --> 00:04:05,920
And so we talk about a fix as being something that you need.
所以我们把“fix”说成是你需要的东西。

86
00:04:05,920 --> 00:04:11,360
Okay, my coffee fix means the coffee that I drink in the morning to survive.
好的，我的“coffee fix”指的是我早上为了撑下去而喝的咖啡。

87
00:04:11,360 --> 00:04:12,360
That's right.
没错。

88
00:04:12,360 --> 00:04:15,800
Okay, so we know the verb to fix is to make something good again, to repair.
好的，我们知道动词“fix”是让东西变好、修理的意思。

89
00:04:15,800 --> 00:04:20,040
But in this case, we're taking fix as a noun and we're saying that it's something that
但在这里，我们把“fix”当作名词用，指的是你

90
00:04:20,040 --> 00:04:24,880
you need, like you said, for example, maybe in the morning you need your English fix and
需要的东西，就像你说的，比如早上你可能需要你的“English fix”，

91
00:04:24,880 --> 00:04:26,280
so you'd listen to EnglishPod.
所以你会听EnglishPod。

92
00:04:26,280 --> 00:04:27,280
Exactly.
正是。

93
00:04:27,280 --> 00:04:29,560
You need it so much, it's like a drug.
你太需要它了，就像毒品一样。

94
00:04:29,560 --> 00:04:30,560
That's right.
没错。

95
00:04:30,560 --> 00:04:31,560
Very good.
很好。

96
00:04:31,560 --> 00:04:34,600
And moving on, they started to talk a little bit more about the details of the business
接着，他们开始多聊了一些生意的细节，

97
00:04:34,600 --> 00:04:41,480
and he mentioned that they want to make this company their sole supplier for cameras.
他提到他们想让这家公司成为他们唯一的相机供应商。

98
00:04:41,480 --> 00:04:45,720
Okay, so sole means only.
好的，所以“sole”意思是唯一的。

99
00:04:45,720 --> 00:04:50,240
But this word supplier is very interesting because it's very similar to vendor.
但“supplier”这个词很有意思，因为它和“vendor”很相似。

100
00:04:50,240 --> 00:04:54,800
So it's basically someone, a company maybe, or a person that supplies you with what you
所以基本上是指某个人，可能是一家公司，或者一个人，为你提供你

101
00:04:54,800 --> 00:04:55,800
need.
需要的东西。

102
00:04:55,800 --> 00:04:57,840
All right, so to supply is to provide for.
好的，所以“to supply”就是提供。

103
00:04:57,840 --> 00:05:04,240
So for example, if I work at a clothing store and I sell lots of nice clothing, I need a
比如，如果我在一家服装店工作，卖很多漂亮的衣服，我需要一个

104
00:05:04,240 --> 00:05:07,160
supplier to bring me the clothes that I sell.
供应商给我带来我卖的衣服。

105
00:05:07,160 --> 00:05:08,720
Otherwise, where am I going to get them from?
否则，我从哪儿弄来呢？

106
00:05:08,720 --> 00:05:10,120
I don't have a factory.
我又没有工厂。

107
00:05:10,120 --> 00:05:11,120
That's right.
没错。

108
00:05:11,120 --> 00:05:15,320
For example, IBM is one of the biggest computer suppliers or manufacturers in the world.
比如，IBM是世界上最大的电脑供应商或制造商之一。

109
00:05:15,320 --> 00:05:16,320
All right.
好的。

110
00:05:16,320 --> 00:05:17,320
Okay.
嗯。

111
00:05:17,320 --> 00:05:24,280
And for the last part of the dialogue, they said, well, I think we can reach an agreement.
在对话的最后部分，他们说，嗯，我想我们可以达成协议。

112
00:05:24,280 --> 00:05:26,960
Let's get started by drafting a new contract.
让我们开始起草一份新合同吧。

113
00:05:26,960 --> 00:05:28,480
They're going to draft a contract.
他们要起草一份合同。

114
00:05:28,480 --> 00:05:33,240
All right, so this is interesting because we don't use the verb to write a contract.
好的，这很有意思，因为我们不用动词“写”合同。

115
00:05:33,240 --> 00:05:37,240
Now you would think, well, of course you write it, but there's a special verb that we use
你可能会想，当然是你写它，但有一个特殊的动词我们用来

116
00:05:37,240 --> 00:05:38,400
with the word contract.
搭配“合同”这个词。

117
00:05:38,400 --> 00:05:43,240
So just remember this phrase together, to draft a contract or my company will draft
所以只要记住这个短语，“to draft a contract”，或者我的公司会起草

118
00:05:43,240 --> 00:05:45,360
a contract and send it to you.
一份合同并寄给你。

119
00:05:45,360 --> 00:05:49,520
This means to prepare a contract in order for someone to sign it.
这意味着准备一份合同，以便某人签署。

120
00:05:49,520 --> 00:05:50,520
That's right.
没错。

121
00:05:50,520 --> 00:05:55,480
So it's basically the same as write, but it's usually used more with contracts to draft
所以基本上和“写”一样，但通常更多用于合同，“to draft

122
00:05:55,480 --> 00:05:56,480
a contract.
a contract”。

123
00:05:56,480 --> 00:05:57,480
Exactly.
正是。

124
00:05:57,480 --> 00:06:00,120
Or maybe you can say to draft up a business plan.
或者你也可以说“to draft up a business plan”。

125
00:06:00,120 --> 00:06:01,120
Exactly.
正是。

126
00:06:01,120 --> 00:06:03,120
So to draft a plan, to draft a contract.
所以“to draft a plan”，“to draft a contract”。

127
00:06:03,120 --> 00:06:07,200
This is basically to write something that has many different points, many different
这基本上是指写一些有很多不同要点、很多不同

128
00:06:07,200 --> 00:06:08,200
strategies.
策略的东西。

129
00:06:08,200 --> 00:06:09,320
Okay, very good.
好的，很好。

130
00:06:09,320 --> 00:06:11,520
So five key words for you there.
所以这里有五个关键词。

131
00:06:11,520 --> 00:06:17,640
And now let's move on to some key phrases on Fluency Builder.
现在让我们进入Fluency Builder的一些关键短语。

132
00:06:17,640 --> 00:06:18,640
Fluency Builder.
Fluency Builder。

133
00:06:18,640 --> 00:06:23,360
Okay, so there are a lot of really, really juicy phrases in today's lesson.
好的，今天的课程中有很多非常非常精彩的短语。

134
00:06:23,360 --> 00:06:26,000
The first one is rest assured.
第一个是“rest assured”。

135
00:06:26,000 --> 00:06:29,120
So we heard this from Michael at the beginning of the dialogue.
我们在对话开头从Michael那里听到了这个。

136
00:06:29,120 --> 00:06:32,400
He said, rest assured that you can count on us.
他说，“rest assured that you can count on us”。

137
00:06:32,400 --> 00:06:33,400
That's right.
没错。

138
00:06:33,400 --> 00:06:34,400
Rest assured.
“Rest assured”。

139
00:06:34,400 --> 00:06:39,720
So this is a phrase that you use to try to give confidence to someone, telling them you
所以这是一个你用来给别人信心的短语，告诉他们你

140
00:06:39,720 --> 00:06:42,760
can trust me, rest assured that I'll be there.
可以信任我，“rest assured that I'll be there”。

141
00:06:42,760 --> 00:06:43,760
Don't worry.
别担心。

142
00:06:43,760 --> 00:06:44,760
Don't worry.
别担心。

143
00:06:44,760 --> 00:06:45,960
So let's hear another example of it.
让我们再听一个例子。

144
00:06:45,960 --> 00:06:49,120
Rest assured, Marco, I will be there to support you.
“Rest assured, Marco, I will be there to support you.”

145
00:06:49,120 --> 00:06:53,160
Okay, so I know that you will be there or I can trust that you'll be there.
好的，所以我知道你会在那里，或者我可以相信你会在那里。

146
00:06:53,160 --> 00:06:54,160
Okay.
嗯。

147
00:06:54,160 --> 00:06:55,160
Very good.
很好。

148
00:06:55,160 --> 00:06:56,280
So to rest assure.
所以“to rest assure”。

149
00:06:56,280 --> 00:07:02,640
Now the second part of it is in that same sentence, well, rest assure that you can count
现在第二部分是在同一个句子里，“rest assure that you can count

150
00:07:02,640 --> 00:07:03,640
on us.
on us”。

151
00:07:03,640 --> 00:07:07,600
Okay, so what does it mean to count on us, to count on me?
好的，那么“to count on us”、“to count on me”是什么意思？

152
00:07:07,600 --> 00:07:11,640
So the verb to count has a couple of different meanings and most of us are familiar with
所以动词“count”有几个不同的意思，我们大多数人都熟悉

153
00:07:11,640 --> 00:07:15,880
the other one, to count numbers, one, two, three, four, five.
另一个意思，数数，一、二、三、四、五。

154
00:07:15,880 --> 00:07:22,520
But here to count on someone, remember that preposition on, means to expect someone to
但这里的“to count on someone”，记住介词“on”，意思是期望某人

155
00:07:22,520 --> 00:07:25,520
do something, to depend on someone.
做某事，依赖某人。

156
00:07:25,520 --> 00:07:26,520
That's right.
没错。

157
00:07:26,520 --> 00:07:32,040
So if you count on someone, means that you depend on them, you rely on them, you can
所以如果你“count on someone”，意味着你依赖他们，你依靠他们，你可以

158
00:07:32,040 --> 00:07:33,620
trust them.
信任他们。

159
00:07:33,620 --> 00:07:40,080
So for example, in the sentence that I just told Marco, rest assured, I will be there.
比如，在我刚才对Marco说的句子里，“rest assured, I will be there”。

160
00:07:40,080 --> 00:07:42,160
You can count on me.
你可以信赖我。

161
00:07:42,160 --> 00:07:46,080
That means you can depend on me, you can expect me to be there.
这意味着你可以依赖我，你可以期待我在那里。

162
00:07:46,080 --> 00:07:47,720
I will not let you down.
我不会让你失望的。

163
00:07:47,720 --> 00:07:48,720
That's right.
没错。

164
00:07:48,720 --> 00:07:49,720
Okay.
好的。

165
00:07:49,720 --> 00:07:54,760
In that same sentence, we have another phrasal verb, rest assured that you can count on
在同一句话中，我们还有另一个短语动词，放心，你可以指望

166
00:07:54,760 --> 00:07:58,360
us to be here for the long run.
我们长期在这里。

167
00:07:58,360 --> 00:07:59,360
The long run.
长期。

168
00:07:59,360 --> 00:08:00,360
All right.
好的。

169
00:08:00,360 --> 00:08:01,840
So we're not actually running here.
所以我们实际上不是在这里跑步。

170
00:08:01,840 --> 00:08:05,560
The long run is a phrase that means for a long time.
“长期”是一个短语，意思是长时间。

171
00:08:05,560 --> 00:08:10,160
So for example, if I'm in an interview and someone asks me, well, we're really interested
例如，如果我在面试中，有人问我，嗯，我们真的很感兴趣

172
00:08:10,160 --> 00:08:13,760
in your resume and we really like you.
你的简历，我们真的很喜欢你。

173
00:08:13,760 --> 00:08:17,940
We want to know, are you available in the long run, in the long term?
我们想知道，你长期来看有空吗，长期来说？

174
00:08:17,940 --> 00:08:18,940
That's right.
没错。

175
00:08:18,940 --> 00:08:23,120
So if you say, yes, I am here for the long run, it means that you are here for a long
所以如果你说，是的，我长期在这里，这意味着你在这里待很长

176
00:08:23,120 --> 00:08:24,600
time.
时间。

177
00:08:24,600 --> 00:08:26,120
Okay.
好的。

178
00:08:26,120 --> 00:08:28,860
And let's move on to our next phrase.
让我们继续下一个短语。

179
00:08:28,860 --> 00:08:33,440
And they're actually, you know, they stopped with a small talk and now they want to get
他们实际上，你知道，停止了闲聊，现在他们想

180
00:08:33,440 --> 00:08:35,120
down to business.
开始谈正事。

181
00:08:35,120 --> 00:08:38,600
You hear this phrase all the time because you don't just walk into a meeting and start
你经常听到这个短语，因为你不会直接走进会议室就开始

182
00:08:38,600 --> 00:08:40,120
talking about business stuff.
谈论业务。

183
00:08:40,120 --> 00:08:42,200
You know, you start with the nice things first.
你知道，你先说些好听的。

184
00:08:42,200 --> 00:08:43,280
You say, how was your weekend?
你说，你周末过得怎么样？

185
00:08:43,280 --> 00:08:44,760
How is your wife?
你妻子怎么样？

186
00:08:44,760 --> 00:08:45,880
How was that game of golf?
那场高尔夫球赛怎么样？

187
00:08:45,880 --> 00:08:50,080
So you're talking about nice small talk, like you just said, Marco, but when you want to
所以你在聊愉快的闲聊，就像你刚才说的，Marco，但当你想

188
00:08:50,080 --> 00:08:54,400
start talking about numbers or products, things like that, that is called business.
开始谈论数字或产品之类的东西时，那才叫业务。

189
00:08:54,400 --> 00:08:57,760
So when you want to start that, you say, let's get down to business.
所以当你想开始时，你说，让我们开始谈正事吧。

190
00:08:57,760 --> 00:08:58,760
That's right.
没错。

191
00:08:58,760 --> 00:08:59,760
That's right.
没错。

192
00:08:59,760 --> 00:09:05,120
So it's a phrase to say, okay, now let's start talking about what we came here to do.
所以这是一个短语，意思是，好了，现在让我们开始谈论我们来这里要做的事。

193
00:09:05,120 --> 00:09:07,440
Start talking about business.
开始谈论业务。

194
00:09:07,440 --> 00:09:11,480
And the last phrase that we have for you, it's a very interesting phrase.
我们为你准备的最后一个短语，是一个非常有趣的短语。

195
00:09:11,480 --> 00:09:17,800
When they were talking about one of the brands of phones, they're saying, I'm glad to hear
当他们谈论其中一个手机品牌时，他们说，我很高兴听到

196
00:09:17,800 --> 00:09:21,760
that Pear has finally jumped on the bandwagon.
Pear 终于跟风了。

197
00:09:21,760 --> 00:09:27,240
Now, Marco, I wish I could tell you, I knew where this phrase came from, but I don't.
现在，Marco，我希望我能告诉你我知道这个短语的来历，但我不知道。

198
00:09:27,240 --> 00:09:29,040
Let's just talk about the word bandwagon first.
我们先谈谈“bandwagon”这个词。

199
00:09:29,040 --> 00:09:34,680
I think bandwagon means something that everyone is doing.
我认为“bandwagon”的意思是大家都在做的事情。

200
00:09:34,680 --> 00:09:35,680
That's right.
没错。

201
00:09:35,680 --> 00:09:42,040
So I think if everyone likes the color purple and all of a sudden you like the color purple,
所以我认为如果每个人都喜欢紫色，然后突然你也喜欢紫色，

202
00:09:42,040 --> 00:09:44,640
then that means you just jumped on the bandwagon.
那就意味着你只是跟风了。

203
00:09:44,640 --> 00:09:45,640
All right.
好的。

204
00:09:45,640 --> 00:09:46,640
I jumped on the bandwagon.
我跟风了。

205
00:09:46,640 --> 00:09:51,160
So you think of a wagon as like, before they had cars, they had wagons.
所以你可以把 wagon 想象成，在汽车出现之前，他们有马车。

206
00:09:51,160 --> 00:09:54,280
They're wooden and they have wheels and they're pulled by a horse.
它们是木制的，有轮子，由马拉着。

207
00:09:54,280 --> 00:09:57,120
And so everyone is on there and they're all going somewhere.
所以每个人都在上面，他们都去某个地方。

208
00:09:57,120 --> 00:09:59,320
And I wasn't on it, but I jumped on the back.
而我本来不在上面，但我跳上了后面。

209
00:09:59,320 --> 00:10:00,880
That means I joined everyone.
这意味着我加入了大家。

210
00:10:00,880 --> 00:10:03,420
I started to do what they're doing.
我开始做他们正在做的事。

211
00:10:03,420 --> 00:10:04,420
That's right.
没错。

212
00:10:04,420 --> 00:10:07,360
So I guess you agree with them or you're going towards in the same direction that everyone
所以我猜你同意他们，或者你朝着大家

213
00:10:07,360 --> 00:10:08,520
else is going.
去的同一个方向前进。

214
00:10:08,520 --> 00:10:09,520
Look at Marco.
看看 Marco。

215
00:10:09,520 --> 00:10:10,520
He just bought an iPhone.
他刚买了一部 iPhone。

216
00:10:10,520 --> 00:10:12,320
Now he's jumped on the bandwagon.
现在他跟风了。

217
00:10:12,320 --> 00:10:13,320
That's right.
没错。

218
00:10:13,320 --> 00:10:15,440
So everyone is going in the same direction.
所以每个人都朝着同一个方向前进。

219
00:10:15,440 --> 00:10:16,880
Everyone is doing the same thing.
每个人都在做同样的事。

220
00:10:16,880 --> 00:10:18,960
Everyone likes the same thing.
每个人都喜欢同样的东西。

221
00:10:18,960 --> 00:10:23,720
So to jump on the bandwagon, you can use it in the business sense.
所以“跟风”这个词，你可以在商业意义上使用它。

222
00:10:23,720 --> 00:10:28,160
For example, if somebody is not agreeing with you or somebody doesn't want to support your
例如，如果有人不同意你，或者有人不想支持你的

223
00:10:28,160 --> 00:10:32,640
project, you can say, I would really appreciate it if you jumped on the bandwagon and supported
项目，你可以说，如果你能跟风支持我们

224
00:10:32,640 --> 00:10:33,720
us on this.
这个项目，我会非常感激。

225
00:10:33,720 --> 00:10:34,720
That's right.
没错。

226
00:10:34,720 --> 00:10:38,600
So it's not always a bad thing, but remember that the verb that is synonymous with this
所以这不总是坏事，但记住，与这个同义的动词

227
00:10:38,600 --> 00:10:39,600
is to conform.
是“顺从”。

228
00:10:39,600 --> 00:10:40,600
Okay.
好的。

229
00:10:40,600 --> 00:10:42,720
To do what everyone else is doing.
做别人都在做的事。

230
00:10:42,720 --> 00:10:43,720
That's right.
没错。

231
00:10:43,720 --> 00:10:44,720
Okay.
好的。

232
00:10:44,720 --> 00:10:45,800
So a lot of interesting things here.
所以这里有很多有趣的东西。

233
00:10:45,800 --> 00:10:57,480
Let's listen to our dialogue one last time.
让我们最后听一遍我们的对话。

234
00:10:57,480 --> 00:10:58,480
Good morning, Angela.
早上好，Angela。

235
00:10:58,480 --> 00:11:00,760
How have you been lately?
你最近怎么样？

236
00:11:00,760 --> 00:11:01,760
Morning Michael.
早上好，Michael。

237
00:11:01,760 --> 00:11:03,800
I've been very busy lately.
我最近很忙。

238
00:11:03,800 --> 00:11:08,840
One of our other vendors is going out of business and I've been searching for a suitable replacement.
我们其中一个供应商要倒闭了，我一直在寻找合适的替代者。

239
00:11:08,840 --> 00:11:12,280
Well rest assured that you can count on us to be here for the long run.
嗯，放心，你可以指望我们长期在这里。

240
00:11:12,280 --> 00:11:13,280
Please sit down.
请坐。

241
00:11:13,280 --> 00:11:14,280
Coffee?
喝咖啡吗？

242
00:11:14,280 --> 00:11:15,280
No, thanks.
不了，谢谢。

243
00:11:15,280 --> 00:11:17,840
I've been trying to cut down on the caffeine.
我一直在努力减少咖啡因的摄入。

244
00:11:17,840 --> 00:11:19,520
I could never do that.
我可做不到。

245
00:11:19,520 --> 00:11:22,640
I'd be a zombie if I didn't have my morning coffee fix.
早上不喝杯咖啡提神，我就像个僵尸。

246
00:11:22,640 --> 00:11:24,400
Let's get down to business then.
那我们直接谈正事吧。

247
00:11:24,400 --> 00:11:25,400
Yes.
好的。

248
00:11:25,400 --> 00:11:29,840
I've come to talk with you about ordering the eight megapixel cameras for our new Mi
我来是想跟你谈谈为我们的新Mi

249
00:11:29,840 --> 00:11:30,840
phone.
手机订购八百万像素摄像头的事。

250
00:11:30,840 --> 00:11:35,680
The demand for phone cameras is growing and Pear has been falling behind in the market.
手机摄像头的需求在增长，而Pear在市场上已经落后了。

251
00:11:35,680 --> 00:11:36,680
That's great.
太好了。

252
00:11:36,680 --> 00:11:39,760
I'm glad to hear that Pear has finally jumped on the bandwagon.
很高兴听到Pear终于跟上了潮流。

253
00:11:39,760 --> 00:11:42,800
Right now our contract is for the five megapixel cameras.
目前我们的合同是五百万像素摄像头。

254
00:11:42,800 --> 00:11:44,880
Is Pear still interested in having those?
Pear还有兴趣要那些吗？

255
00:11:44,880 --> 00:11:45,880
No.
不。

256
00:11:45,880 --> 00:11:49,200
We're changing all the cameras to eight megapixels.
我们正在把所有摄像头换成八百万像素的。

257
00:11:49,200 --> 00:11:54,400
We were hoping that by making your company our sole supplier for cameras, we could negotiate
我们希望通过让贵公司成为我们摄像头的独家供应商，来协商

258
00:11:54,400 --> 00:11:55,640
a better deal.
一个更好的价格。

259
00:11:55,640 --> 00:11:56,640
Surely.
当然。

260
00:11:56,640 --> 00:12:02,720
Let's get started by drafting a new contract.
我们开始起草一份新合同吧。

261
00:12:02,720 --> 00:12:05,920
So talking about purchasing, it's actually a very interesting position.
说到采购，这其实是一个非常有趣的职位。

262
00:12:05,920 --> 00:12:12,660
I think many, or almost all companies, big companies have this position where not only
我认为很多，或者说几乎所有公司，大公司都有这个职位，不仅

263
00:12:12,660 --> 00:12:16,840
do they have to, maybe if they're in retailing, they have to purchase the goods that they
是零售业需要采购要卖的商品，

264
00:12:16,840 --> 00:12:18,760
will sell, but also in offices.
办公室也需要。

265
00:12:18,760 --> 00:12:23,640
For example, who buys the paper, the printers, the copiers, everything for the office?
比如，谁买纸、打印机、复印机，以及办公室的一切用品？

266
00:12:23,640 --> 00:12:24,640
That's right.
没错。

267
00:12:24,640 --> 00:12:29,960
This is a very important position, as you say, because this person can save a company
正如你所说，这是一个非常重要的职位，因为如果这个人了解合适的供应商，

268
00:12:29,960 --> 00:12:33,320
a lot of money if the person knows the right vendors.
就能为公司省下很多钱。

269
00:12:33,320 --> 00:12:34,320
That's right.
没错。

270
00:12:34,320 --> 00:12:38,120
If the only vendors you know are selling things at very high prices, then that's not very
如果你只知道那些卖高价东西的供应商，那对你或你的生意

271
00:12:38,120 --> 00:12:40,040
good for you or for your business.
都不太好。

272
00:12:40,040 --> 00:12:43,120
But if you know all the inside secrets, you know all the good vendors, then maybe you're
但如果你知道所有内部秘诀，了解所有好供应商，那你可能

273
00:12:43,120 --> 00:12:44,840
going to be able to save a lot of money.
就能省下很多钱。

274
00:12:44,840 --> 00:12:45,840
That's right.
没错。

275
00:12:45,840 --> 00:12:49,520
I think this position is also a lot broader than just this.
我认为这个职位比这还要广泛得多。

276
00:12:49,520 --> 00:12:54,080
Maybe someone can also help us out on the website, EnglishPod.com.
也许有人也能在我们的网站EnglishPod.com上帮帮忙。

277
00:12:54,080 --> 00:12:55,080
You can explain.
你可以解释一下。

278
00:12:55,080 --> 00:12:58,080
Maybe if you're a purchasing manager, you can tell us what your job entails.
如果你是个采购经理，你可以告诉我们你的工作内容是什么。

279
00:12:58,080 --> 00:13:01,120
Or if you know a purchasing manager, what does that person do?
或者如果你认识一个采购经理，那个人是做什么的？

280
00:13:01,120 --> 00:13:02,120
That's right.
没错。

281
00:13:02,120 --> 00:13:04,480
We're very curious to know, and we hope that you'll be able to use some of these new words
我们很好奇，也希望你能用上这些新词

282
00:13:04,480 --> 00:13:05,620
and phrases.
和短语。

283
00:13:05,620 --> 00:13:07,640
If you want to practice, check us out, EnglishPod.com.
如果你想练习，就来我们的网站EnglishPod.com看看吧。

284
00:13:07,640 --> 00:13:08,640
All right.
好的。

285
00:13:08,640 --> 00:13:09,640
We'll see you guys there.
我们那儿见。

286
00:13:09,640 --> 00:13:10,640
Thanks.
谢谢。

287
00:13:10,640 --> 00:13:39,500
Robert Fukunaga, EnglishPod number two, EnglishPod number two.
Robert Fukunaga，EnglishPod第二期，EnglishPod第二期。
